INSTALL - Anteater Chess

=== User Package (Chess_V1.0.tar.gz) ===

No installation required. A pre-compiled Linux binary is included.

1. Unpack:
     tar -xvzf Chess_V1.0.tar.gz

2. Run:
     cd Chess_V1.0/bin
     ./chess

Note: If running over SSH, X11 forwarding is required to display the GUI:
  Connect with: ssh -X username@server
  On macOS clients, XQuartz must be installed: https://www.xquartz.org


=== Source Package (Chess_V1.0_src.tar.gz) ===

Requirements:
  GCC 9.0 or later
  GNU Make
  SDL2, SDL2_ttf, SDL2_image

Installing SDL2 dependencies:
  Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
    sudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev libsdl2-ttf-dev libsdl2-image-dev
  Linux (Fedora/RHEL):
    sudo dnf install SDL2-devel SDL2_ttf-devel SDL2_image-devel
  macOS (Homebrew):
    brew install sdl2 sdl2_ttf sdl2_image

1. Unpack:
     tar -xvzf Chess_V1.0_src.tar.gz

2. Build:
     cd Chess_V1.0_src
     make

3. Run:
     cd bin
     ./chess

To run tests:
  make test

To clean build files:
  make clean

To uninstall, delete the directory:
  rm -rf Chess_V1.0_src/
